For the first time — and probably not the last — a scientific breakthrough enabled by artificial intelligence (AI) has been recognized with a Nobel prize. The 2024 chemistry Nobel was awarded to John Jumper and Demis Hassabis at Google DeepMind in London, for developing a game-changing
AI tool for predicting protein structures called AlphaFold
, and David Baker, at the University of Washington in Seattle, for his work on computational protein design, which has been
bolstered by Al in the past few years
.
